    "text": [
        "The office is no longer the only workplace as many people consider working from home. Some might argue that most employees should change their workplace from the office to home. In my opinion, the benefits of working from home can certainly outweigh the drawbacks due to the following reasons:",
        "Working from home is a lot more comfortable for many people. Employees can save time and money because they do not have to travel often, so everyone has more time for work and themselves. Commuting less will also help reduce traffic jams and pollutants in our environment. Besides, working from home does not mean staying indoors all day. People can choose to work in their garden or backyard, wherever it makes them feel convenient to work. Furthermore, employees are less stressed because they can decide when to work and rest. These will help to bring better performance to the tasks.",
        "There are still some downsides to working from home. For example, working in a personal space reduces face-to-face interactions between colleagues. However, the problem is solved thanks to the Internet. As it is now, people from all over the world can easily communicate and work with others from long distances. Another disadvantage is that external factors can distract some people from work. This requires employees to be highly alert about what they should and should not do with their paid work.",
        "In short, working from home should be encouraged because the advantages outweigh the disadvantages."
